%% Slot-level state machine for individual 30-minute slots in Available Bookings.
%% Shows the 6+ states a slot can be in (5 Type-field states + (empty) + Blocked
%% as an orthogonal flag), and the overwrite priority rules between them.

stateDiagram-v2
    direction LR

    [*] --> available: Slot generated<br/>by script 01

    available --> pending: Reserved as buffer<br/>(script 03)
    available --> setup: Booking with setup<br/>checkbox checked
    available --> teardown: Booking confirmed<br/>(always applied after)
    available --> booking: Within [Start, End)<br/>of confirmed booking

    pending --> setup: Next booking claims<br/>the buffer
    pending --> available: Rejection cleanup<br/>(script 05)

    setup --> available: Rejection cleanup<br/>(only if booking above<br/>was rejected)

    teardown --> available: Rejection cleanup<br/>(only if booking below<br/>was rejected)

    booking --> available: Rejection cleanup<br/>(via clearing Booked Slots)

    note left of pending
        Invisible to requestors.
        Convertible: only state that
        a future Setup can overwrite.
    end note

    note right of setup
        Setup can overwrite Pending,
        but NOT Setup/Teardown/Booking
        from another booking.
    end note

    note right of booking
        Highest priority.
        Nothing overwrites a slot
        that has Booked Slots populated.
    end note
